26/10/2006
PLOVDIV, Bulgaria -- The country's anti-mafia services have seized over 50kg of cocaine in the central city of Plovdiv, following a joint action US and Turkish authorities. 
Plovdiv regional prosecutor Andrey Atanasov said on Wednesday (October 25th) that the drugs were found in packages of 1kg each, hidden in a store in a southern industrial zone. 
Police reportedly are searching for six Bulgarians linked to the case.
In other news, Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev officially named Meglena Kuneva as Bulgaria's representative in the European Commission on Thursday. 
She has been serving as minister of European affairs. 
(Mediapool, Focus Sega - 26/10/06; Darik - 25/10/06)
